<!-- Game Description Sectional -->

<table border="0" width="100%" id="table16" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 8pt; color: #FFFFFF; font-weight: bold; text-align: left; background-color: #333333; border-left: 2px solid #000000; border-right: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-top: 2px solid #000000; border-bottom: 2px solid #FFFFFF">
                  <br>A crossword is a word puzzle that normally takes the form of a square or rectangular grid of white and shaded squares. The goal is to fill the white squares with letters, forming words or phrases, by solving clues which lead to the answers. In languages that are written left-to-right, the answer words and phrases are placed in the grid from left to right and from top to bottom. The shaded squares are used to separate the words or phrases.
                  <br><br>Squares in which answers begin are usually numbered. The clues are then referred to by these numbers and a direction, for example, "4-Across" or "20-Down". At the end of the clue the total number of letters is sometimes given, depending on the style of puzzle and country of publication. Some crosswords will also indicate the number of words in a given answer, should there be more than one.
                  <br><br>Puzzle Mania features a numbers crossword puzzle game and assorted variants (Crossword Number Place, Skeleton Crossword & Number Crossword) which requires logic and quick thinking. Ply your guile on a 9x9 tiled board. The game features a complete tutorial in japanese.
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Manufacturer's description:</u><br>
                  <br>Depth and simplicity that anyone can enjoy . And exhilaration when you clear the problem . Puzzle game collection of wonderful elements required for puzzle game was included all comes up! Puzzle that is included is three . " Number Place " and " skeleton " and " number crossword " . You can As you clear each problem , to challenge further challenges . And when you have solved the mystery of all , you can play the brain stimulation type puzzle types of completely different puzzle of three . The challenge to challenge Kimon of three + a, Aim a true " Puzzle Mania " !
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Features:</u><br>
			<ul><li>First person perspective.</li>
			<li>2D graphics</li>
			<li>Cartoon graphics</li>
			<li>Crossword theme.</li></ul>
</td>

	</tr>
	</table>
